<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6484397>
    dc:description "Fig. 20. Fish otoliths from the US middle and upper Eocene. A–C. “Neobythites” rotundus Müller, 1999, Piney Point F., sand and gravel pit, Bottoms Bridge, loc. 22 of Müller, Virginia (IRSNB P 10100–10102). D–E. Apogon sp., “Stone City beds”, Stone City Bluff, Brazos River, Texas (IRSNB P 10103–10104). F–J. “Apogon” americanus (Dante & Frizzell, 1965), “Stone City beds”, Texas. F–G. Stone City Bluff, Brazos River, sample 2 from bed P (IRSNB P 10105–10106). H–J. Alabama Ferry, on Trinity River, North (IRSNB P 10107–10109). 1 = ventral view; 2 = inner view. Scale bars = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation <https://zenodo.org/record/6484397/files/figure.png> ;
    a fabio:Figure .
